'''Angolan Union for Peace, Democracy and Development''' ({{lang-pt|União Angolana Pela Paz Democracia e Desenvolvimento}}, UADPP) is a [[political party]] in [[Angola]]. The party was founded on February 16, 1994.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cne.ao/partidos.cfm|title=Comissão Nacional Eleitoral de Angola|website=www.cne.ao|access-date=2017-07-06}}</ref> The party is a member of the coalition [[New Democracy (Angola)|New Democracy]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Amundsen|first=Inge|last2=Weimer|first2=Markus|date=2008|title=Opposition Parties and the 2008 Parliamentary Elections in Angola|url=http://www.cmi.no/publications/file/?3103=opposition-parties-and-the-upcoming-2008|journal=CMI Working Paper|language=en|volume=WP 2008:9}}</ref>

