The Baltic Air Surveillance Network's Regional Airspace Surveillance Coordination Centre (RASCC) is located in [[Karmėlava]] and reports to [[NATO]]'s CAOC Uedem.

* '''Regional Airspace Surveillance Coordination Centre''' (RASCC), in [[Karmėlava]]
** ([[Estonian Air Force]]) Air Operations Centre, at [[Ämari Air Base]]
*** Radar Station, in [[Levalõpme]], with [[Ground Master 403|GM 403]]
*** Radar Station, in [[Otepää]], with [[Ground Master 403|GM 403]]
*** Radar Station, in [[Kellavere]], with [[AN/TPS-77]]
** ([[Latvian Air Force]]) Air Operations Centre, at [[Lielvārde Air Base]]
*** 1st Radiotechnical (Radar) Post, at [[Lielvārde Air Base]], with [[AN/TPS-77]]
*** 2nd Radiotechnical (Radar) Post, in [[Audriņi]], with [[AN/TPS-77]]
*** 3rd Radiotechnical (Radar) Post, in [[Ventspils|Čalas]], with [[AN/TPS-77]]
** ([[Lithuanian Air Force]]) Airspace Operations Centre, in [[Karmėlava]]
*** 1st Radar Post, in [[Prienai|Antaveršis]], with [[AN/TPS-77]]
*** 3rd Radar Post, in [[Šilutė|Degučiai]], with [[AN/TPS-77]]
*** 4th Radar Post, in [[Ignalina|Ceikiškės]], with [[AN/TPS-77]]

