The Cissianti were a tribe of [[Iranian peoples|Iranian]] [[Nomad|Nomads]] who likely spoke a [[Sarmatians|Sarmatian]] language of the [[Scythians|Scythian]] family.  They are mentioned by [[Pliny the Elder]] as living north of the [[Amazons]] and [[Hyperborea|Hyperboreans]], with the [[Cimmerians|Cimmeri]], [[Acae (Ancient People)|Acae]], [[Georgili (Ancient People)|Georgili]], [[Moschia|Moschi]], [[Cercetae]], [[Phoristae]], and [[Rimphaces]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MRB5AAAAQBAJ&pg=PA94&lpg=PA94&dq=Cissianti&source=bl&ots=un1dAN0y9g&sig=PfjTUi71ppptTVWebGxE89hJ5J8&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjAkPr5wLbVAhVHs1QKHQQbD8oQ6AEIOjAE#v=onepage&q=Cissianti&f=false|title=Race and Ethnicity in the Classical World: An Anthology of Primary Sources in Translation|last=Kennedy|first=Rebecca F.|last2=Roy|first2=C. Sydnor|last3=Goldman|first3=Max L.|date=2013-09-01|publisher=Hackett Publishing|isbn=9781624660900|language=en}}</ref>

