'''Cliathairi''' were the professional "guards" around a king,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=AislDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA92#v=onepage&q&f=false |title=Early Medieval Ireland 400-1200 |author= Daibhi O Croinin}}</ref> who formed the backbone of an army in the [[Gaelic warfare]] of [[Medieval Ireland]], having chosen [[military service]] as a career. 

