{{Politics of Gambia}}
'''Parliamentary elections''' were held in [[the Gambia]] on 17 January 2002. They were boycotted by several opposition parties, including the [[United Democratic Party (Gambia)|United Democratic Party]].<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/africa/1768466.stm Gambia poll landslide] BBC News, 18 January 2002</ref> As a result, the ruling [[Alliance for Patriotic Reorientation and Construction]] of [[Heads of State of the Gambia|President]] [[Yahya Jammeh]] ran unopposed in 33 of the 48 elected seats,<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/africa/1765612.stm Poor turnout for Gambia polls] BBC News, 17 January 2002</ref> and won 12 of the 15 seats in which they had opposition.
In seats where there was a vote, turnout was 56.4%.
