[[File:1991 CPA 6373.jpg|300px|thumb|Modern keyed ganurags (upper instrument) on 1991 USSR Postage stamp showing Latvian traditional instruments]]
The '''ganurags''' (or '''ganu rags''' – "shepherd's horn) is a Latvian [[clarinet]]-like [[musical instrument]] with a cylindrical wooden body ending in an animal's horn.<ref>{{cite web |first=Amanda |last=Jātniece |title=A primer on Latvian folk instruments |url=http://latviansonline.com/a-primer-on-latvian-folk-instruments/ |accessdate=November 28, 2016 |website=Latvians Online |date=July 16, 2001}}</ref> In the modern era the instrument was made more sophisticated with classical additions like keywork.<ref>{{cite book|title=The Clarinet|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=w4QJAQAAMAAJ|year=1992|publisher=Department of Music, Idaho State University|page=66}}</ref>
==See also== *[[Birbynė]] *[[Zhaleika]] *[[Hornpipe (instrument)|Hornpipe]]
