<!-- bottom --> | title = President | before_election = [[Alassane Ouattara]] | before_party = Rally of the Republicans | posttitle = | after_election = TBD | after_party = TBD }} {{Politics of Côte d'Ivoire}}
'''Presidential elections''' will be held in [[Ivory Coast]] on 31 October 2020. Incumbent President [[Alassane Ouattara]] has announced he will not run again after being president for two terms (2010–2015 and 2015–2020).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/ivory-coast-president-alassane-ouattara-vows-step-down-2020-1599444|title=Politics Ivory Coast President Alassane Ouattara vows to step down in 2020|publisher=International Business Times|date=January 5, 2017}}</ref>
==Electoral system== The [[President of the Ivory Coast]] and the [[Vice-President of Ivory Coast|Vice-President]] will be elected on the same ticket with a five-year mandate using the [[two-round system]], with 50% simple majority required to avoid a run-off. According to the [[Constitution of Ivory Coast|2016 constitution]], candidates are limited to two consecutive terms as President and Vice-President.
