The '''Magosian''' is the name given by [[archaeologist]]s to an [[archaeological industry|industry]] found in southern and eastern [[Africa]]. It dates to between 10,000 and 6,000 years BC and is distinguished from its predecessors by the use of [[microlith]]s and small [[blade]]s.  

In 1953, [[J. Desmond Clark]] found a notable site of Magosian artifacts at [[Kalambo Falls]], on what is now the border between  [[Zambia]] and [[Tanzania]].

