{{Infobox mine | name = Mittersill mine | image = | width = | caption = | pushpin_map = | pushpin_label = | pushpin_map_caption = | coordinates = | place = [[Mittersill]] | subdivision_type = [[Town]] | state/province = [[Salzburg (state)|Salzburg]] | country = [[Austria]] | owner = [[Wolfram Bergbau und Hütten]] | stock_exchange = None | stock_code = [[Privately-held company|Private]] | official website = | acquisition year = | products = [[Tungsten]] | financial year = 2009 | amount = 1,200 tonnes of [[tungsten]] | opening year = 1967 | closing year = }} The '''Mittersill mine''' is a large mine located in [[Mittersill]], in the Western part of [[Austria]] in [[Salzburg (state)|Salzburg]], 30&nbsp;km South of [[Kitzbühel]] and 339&nbsp;km South - West of the capital, [[Vienna]]. Mittersill represents the largest [[tungsten]] reserves in [[Austria]] having estimated reserves of 6.1 million tonnes of ore grading 0.5% pure tungsten.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eswww.rhul.ac.uk/geode/ABCD/Mittersill.html|title=Mittersill|year=2010|publisher=rhul.ac.uk|accessdate=2010-09-06}}{{dead link|date=September 2018}}</ref><ref name="Mittersill">{{cite web|url=http://www.wolfram.at/wolfram_at/wEnglisch/unternehmen/index3223655460navidW2618000000000.html?navid=1|title=WBH History|publisher=Wolfram Bergbau und Hütten|accessdate=2010-09-06}}</ref> The mine produces around 1,200 tonnes of tungsten/year.<ref name="Mittersill"/>
== History == Exploration started in 1967. Production started as an [[open pit]] mine (eastern field) in 1976. Since 1986 only underground mining in the westfield is performed. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mineralienatlas.de/lexikon/index.php/%D6sterreich/Salzburg/Zell%20am%20See%2C%20Bezirk%20%28Pinzgau%29/Mittersill/Felbertal/Scheelitlagerst%E4tte|title=German mineral atlas|accessdate=2017-02-02}}</ref>
