{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}} {{Infobox film | name = The Children of Genghis | image = The Children of Genghis.jpg | caption = Film poster | director = [[Zolbayar Dorj]] | producer = | writer = Zolbayar Dorj | starring = [[Brittany Belt]] | music = Ulziibayar Shatar | cinematography = Angarag Davaasuren | editing = Gantulga Urtnasan | distributor = | released = {{film date|2017|5|21|[[2017 Cannes Film Festival|Cannes]]|2017|6|30|Mongolia|df=yes}} | runtime = 90 minutes | country = Mongolia | language = Mongolian | budget = }}
'''''The Children of Genghis''''' is a 2017 Mongolian [[drama film]] directed by [[Zolbayar Dorj]]. It was selected as the Mongolian entry for the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[90th Academy Awards]], but it was not nominated.<ref name="THR">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-92-films-submitted-foreign-language-film-academy-award-1046070 |title=Oscars: 92 Films Submitted in Foreign-Language Category |last=Kilday |first=Gregg |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=5 October 2017 |accessdate=5 October 2017}}</ref>
==Plot== A young boy in the Mongolian countryside trains for a horse race.
==Cast== * [[Brittany Belt]] as Sarah Jones ( UNICEF officer) * [[Ankhnyam Ragchaa]] as Tsetsegee (Dambii's wife) * [[Batmend Baast]] as Dambii
